Source: Canada - Health Canada SARS website 8 Apr 2003 [edited]
<http://www.hc-sc.gc.ca/english/protection/warnings/sars/update24.html>

Update 24 - Severe Acute Respiratory Syndrome 8 Apr 2003 5:00 PM
Latest Canadian Numbers on SARS
As of 8 Apr 2003, Health Canada has received reports of 232 probable or
suspect cases of severe acute respiratory syndrome (SARS) in Canada. There
have been 10 deaths in Canada. All Canadian cases have occurred in persons
who have traveled to Asia or had contact with SARS cases in the household
or in a health-care setting.
The details of the cases to date are as follows:
Ontario is reporting 91 probable and 99 suspect cases. All cases have
occurred in persons who have traveled to Asia or had contact with SARS
cases in the household or in a health-care setting.
British Columbia is reporting 3 probable and 26 suspect cases.
New Brunswick is reporting 2 suspect cases.
Saskatchewan is reporting 1 suspect case.
Alberta is reporting 6 suspect cases.
Prince Edward Island is reporting 4 suspect cases.
These numbers are accurate as of 1:00 PM EDST, 8 Apr 2003.
